definition.value: This is an AE which refers a transient abnormal enlargement of the muscle not caused by a tumor.
This is an AE which is a highly aggressive form of cancer that develops from mesenchymal cells that have failed to fully differentiate into myocytes of skeletal muscle.
This is an AE which is a type of muscle loss (muscle atrophy) that occurs with aging and/or immobility.
This is an AE which is benign tumors that are composed of fibrous or connective tissue.
This is an AE which is a non-atherosclerotic, non-inflammatory disease of the blood vessels that causes abnormal growth within the wall of an artery.
This is an AE which is a medical condition characterized by chronic widespread pain and a heightened pain response to pressure.

This is an AE which is a malignant mesenchymal tumour derived from fibrous connective tissue and characterized by the presence of immature proliferating fibroblasts or undifferentiated anaplastic spindle cells in a storiform pattern.

This is an AE which is a pathological wound healing in which connective tissue replaces normal parenchymal tissue to the extent that it goes unchecked, leading to considerable tissue remodelling and the formation of permanent scar tissue.

This is an AE which is a pathological wound healing in which connective tissue replaces normal tendinous parenchymal tissue to the extent that it goes unchecked, leading to considerable tissue remodelling and the formation of permanent scar tissue.
This is an AE which is a benign, non-neoplastic proliferative process that is relatively common in the long bones of skeletally immature adolescents.
This is an AE which is a benign skin growth.
This is an AE which is a fracture of the lower legs bones meaning either or both of the tibia and fibula.
This is an AE which is an inability or impairment of an individual to perform tasks that require a degree of manual dexterity.
This is an AE which is a function that involves specific movements of the bodies muscles to perform a certain task but it has dysfunction.
This is an AE which is a permanent shortening of a extremity  muscle or joint.
This is an AE which is a form of extremity cell injury which results in the premature death of cells in living tissue by autolysis.
This is an AE which is the removal of a limb or foot by trauma, medical illness, or surgery.

This is an AE which is a medical condition in which damage to the anterior interosseous nerve (AIN), a distal motor and sensory branch of the median nerve, classically with severe weakness of the pincer movement of the thumb and index finger, and can cause transient pain in the wrist (the terminal, sensory branch of the AIN innervates the bones of the carpal tunnel).
This is an AE which is a bone fracture which occurs when a fragment of bone tears away from the main mass of bone as a result of physical trauma.
This is an AE which is a resilient and smooth elastic tissue and its development is disorder.
This is an AE which exists when the capacity of the pelvis is inadequate to allow the fetus to negotiate the birth canal.
This is an AE which is a fracture of any of the seven cervical vertebrae in the neck.
This is an AE which is inflammation of cartilage.
This is an AE which is calcification (accumulation of calcium salts) in hyaline cartilage and/or fibrocartilage.
This is an AE which refers to a skeletal disorder caused by one of myriad genetic mutations that can affect the development of cartilage.
This is an AE which is a bone sarcoma, a primary cancer composed of cells derived from transformed cells that produce cartilage.
This is an AE which is a bone fracture of the clavicle.
This is an AE which is a medical term meaning pain in the coccyx or tailbone area, often brought on by a fall onto the coccyx or by persistent irritation usually from sitting.
This is an AE which refers a fracture in which the bone has broken into several pieces.
This is an AE which is a collapse of a vertebra. It may be due to trauma or due to a weakening of the vertebra (compare with burst fracture).
This is an AE which is a benign inflammatory condition affecting the upper costochondral junctions and costosternal joints.
This is an AE which refers the bone remodeling is the process of laying down new bone material by cells named osteoblasts.
This is an AE which represents a relatively uncommon injury in the non-elderly population often resulting from high-energy trauma.
This is an AE which is a bone fracture that involves the femur.
This is an AE which is a disorder of the foot that can be congenital or acquired.
This is an AE which includes lisfranc fracture,Jones fracture , march fracture , calcaneal fracture,  broken toe and  cuneiform fracture.
This is an AE which is one of the serious neurological complications in ACH.
This is an AE which is the region of the upper limb between the elbow and the wrist which is fracture.
This is an AE which is when a fractured bone does not heal properly.

This is an AE which is broadly classified as surgical or conservative, the latter basically referring to any non-surgical procedure, such as pain management, immobilization or other non-surgical stabilization.
This is an AE which is a fracture of the coccyx.
This is an AE which is a scaphoid fracture—a fracture of the scaphoid bone, one of the carpal bones.
This is an AE which is a break of the humerus bone in the upper arm.
This is an AE which is a medical condition combining clubbing and periostitis of the small hand joints, especially the distal interphalangeal joints and the metacarpophalangeal joints.

This is an AE which is the second most common knee injury caused by inflammation located on the lateral aspect of the knee due to friction between the iliotibial band and the lateral epicondyle of the femur.
This is an AE which is the separation of ilium into two or more pieces under the action of stress.
This is an AE which is the separation of limb into two or more pieces under the action of stress.
This is an AE which is the separation of lower limb into two or more pieces under the action of stress.
This is an AE which can directly produce massive RPH leading to hemorrhagic death.
This is an AE which is pain along the inside edge of the shinbone (tibia) due to inflammation of tissue in the area.
